   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Remarks
</p>
      <p>
This species was originally described by 
Takakuwa (1941)
from 
Hokkaido
Island with several collection points (Sapporo, Rumoi, Mt. Daisetu). Unfortunately he did not denote the precise 
type
locality. Nevertheless 
<tp:taxon-name>
Levizonus montanus
</tp:taxon-name>
appears to be spread in central part of 
Hokkaido
(see 
Tanabe 1994
).
</p>
